President Trump held a meeting with Republican members of the House Ways and Means Committee to discuss the proposed tax cuts. He emphasized the importance of tax cuts for the economy and stated that it would be the biggest tax cut in US history. The President also called on Congress to terminate the diversity visa lottery program and end chain migration in order to improve national security. He expressed his desire to have a tax reform bill on his desk by Thanksgiving and highlighted some key aspects of the proposed tax cuts, such as doubling the standard deduction and reducing income tax rates for individuals. The President also mentioned the goal of making America globally competitive by slashing the corporate tax rate and implementing a territorial system. He believes that the proposed tax cuts will lead to economic growth, job creation, and increased wages.